att(con115, pro95).  % [rebuttal] conf=75 — [symmetric rebuttal] A presents marijuana as medically beneficial, whereas B claims legalization harms the Pueblo community, yielding opposite conclusions about its overall impact.
att(con70, pro95).  % [rebuttal] conf=80 — [symmetric rebuttal] A says marijuana is a natural medical substitute, while B claims it is more toxic than cigarettes, directly opposing the health assessment.
att(con12, pro95).  % [rebuttal] conf=80 — [symmetric rebuttal] A’s claim of medical benefit conflicts with B’s assertion that marijuana is terrible for physical health, making the conclusions incompatible.